I just had absolutely the best meal of my culinary life. I can honestly say, as a Peruvian, it is hard to find good and authentic Peruvian food in Chicago. Well, I no longer have to look! I have found it. Our server, Rosa, was as knowledgeable about the menu as any Peruvian chef and we even discovered she was Guatemalan! We started out with papa rellena which was cooked perfectly. Then we enjoyed an exquisite lomo saltado followed by a flan for dessert. We washed it down with several Inca Kolas and a bottle of wine which we brought (BYOB). The prices are extremely reasonable and the wait staff and chef were outstanding. Rosa even asked the chef to come out to discuss Peruvian food! What a fantastic night we will never forget! Rosa for President!

The food was okay,, but for the wait and the price it was sub par.  I came here for my brothers birthday as a group of 8. We had done research beforehand and the good reviews led us here.  We waited over an hour and 20 minutes for our food. I admit it could have been worse, but the reward for our wait was unsatisfying. The food was underwhelming and extremely overpriced. Take the dish in the photo. $20 for a cup of rice and mediocre chicken breast. I should also mention that it was supposed to come with yucca fries, but they forgot to bring it. They did bring it upon asking, however.  The service was also another weak point of the experience. As said we waited far too long for our food. When it did eventually come it was not all at once. Leaving some awkwardly letting their food get cold while others had nothing to eat. When it came time for the check we were once again awkwardly waiting for far too long. I will say, however, that all of the servers were very kind, but they simply seemed completely unprepared and overwhelmed.  All in all these factors combined to make our time here an overall negative experience that warrants a 2 star review.

I finally decided to try this place after driving past it on my way to work everyday. The restaurant has a classy, but cozy feel. Great spot for a date. I regretted getting my food to-go. The host was very friendly and patient. The service was surprisingly fast- less than 10 minutes! Food was delicious and portions were generous. They also gave me house-made bread with some guacamole like sauce. I will be going back again!

Eh it used to be a shady dive bar.  Now it's a shady Peruvian restaurant. I do not care who owns it but what I can tell you is the food would be better at Panda Express.  The ceviche had 4 WARM shrimp and like 10 avocados. No Chips.hmmmm  Our next curses came with ugly looking fettuccini in a stir fry with again smelly stinky shrimps. My dish was a steak and it wasn't bad but it was chewy. The vegetables were completely outta a can. Will not even be back no matter how close it is to my house. I had 0 desire to eat the fettuccini or mushroom 'risotto' on my dish. The actual vegetable melody of carrots etc. was hard as a rock and cold. Pitiful. And we got a 'free dessert' but the ceviche was just over charged by 5$ to appear as a free dessert. Even with a grouping it was 47$. Not good at all.  Also the restaurant was entirely empty. Like we were the ONLY people there. How did I have an empty water glass lol
